P1-RevShop
==========

Application Overview

RevShop is a secure console-based e-commerce application for both buyers and sellers. Buyers can browse products, manage shopping carts, place orders, and review purchases. Sellers can manage inventory, add products, view orders, and monitor stock levels. The application is designed with a modular architecture that can be extended to a microservices-based web application in future phases.

Core Functional Requirements:
--------
As a Buyer, I should be able to:

Register on the platform
Login using email and password

View product details including price, description, and user reviews
Browse products by category or search by keywords
Add or remove products from cart with quantity

Checkout and enter shipping and billing information
Receive in-app notifications when an order is placed
View order history

Review and rate products
Save products as favorites
Make payment using simulated payment methods
-----
As a Seller, I should be able to:

Register as a seller with email, password, and business details
Login using email and password

Manage product inventory (add, update, delete)
Add new products with price, description, and category
View all placed orders for their products

Receive in-app notifications when a user places an order

Set discounted price along with maximum retail price (MRP)

View product reviews and ratings
Set inventory threshold values and get console alerts when stock is low

Standard Functional Scope:

Registered users should be able to log in, change password, and request forgotten password recovery (through security questions or password hint).

P2-RevPlay
===========

Application Overview

RevPlay is a console-based music streaming application that allows users to access a library of songs, artists, playlists, albums, and podcasts. Users can search for content, mark favorites, manage playlists, and simulate music playback. Musicians/artists can create profiles to showcase their music. The application is designed with a modular architecture that can be extended to a microservices-based web/mobile application in future phases.

Core Functional Requirements

As a User, I should be able to:

Register and create an account
Login to my account
Search the library of songs, artists, playlists, podcasts, and albums by keywords
Browse content by categories (genre, artist, album)
Mark songs as favorites
View my favorite songs list
Simulate music player controls (play, pause, skip, repeat) - text-based simulation
Create private or public playlists with name and description
Add songs to my playlists
Remove songs from my playlists
View all my playlists
Update playlist details (name, description, privacy settings)
Delete playlists created by me
View public playlists created by other users
View recently played songs
View listening history


As a Musician/Artist, I should be able to:

Register as an artist with email, password, and artist details
Login to my account
Create and manage my artist profile (bio, genre, social media links)
Upload songs with details (title, album, genre, duration, release date)
Create albums and add songs to albums
View my uploaded songs and albums
Update song/album information
Delete my songs/albums
View play count and statistics for my songs
See which users have added my songs to favorites
Standard Functional Scope

Registered users (both listeners and artists) should be able to log in, change password, and request forgotten password recovery (through security questions or password hint).

P3- RevWorkforce
========

Application Overview

Rev Workforce is a console-based Human Resource Management (HRM) application designed to streamline employee management, leave tracking, and performance review processes. The system supports three user roles: Employees, Managers, and Admins, each with specific functionalities. The application is designed with a modular architecture that can be extended to a microservices-based web application in future phases.

Core Functional Requirements

As an Employee, I should be able to:

Authentication & Profile:

Login to my account using employee ID and password
Edit basic profile information (phone number, address, emergency contact)
View my reporting manager details

Leave Management Module:

View available leave balance (Casual, Sick, Paid leaves)
Apply for leave with date range, leave type, and reason
View all applied leaves with status (Pending/Approved/Rejected)
View company holiday calendar
View manager's name and contact while applying for leave
Cancel pending leave applications
Receive in-app notifications when leave is approved or rejected

Performance Management Module:

Create annual performance review document including:
Key deliverables achieved
Major accomplishments
Areas of improvement
Self-assessment rating
Set goals and targets for the year with:
Goal description
Deadline
Weightage/Priority (High/Medium/Low)
Success metrics
View goals progress and status
Update goal progress periodically
View manager's feedback on performance review
Receive notifications when manager provides feedback

Additional Features:

View upcoming employee birthdays
View work anniversaries of colleagues
View company announcements
Access employee directory
As a Manager, I should be able to:

Note: All managers are employees, so they have access to all employee features plus the following:

Leave Management Module:

View list of direct reportees (employees reporting to me)
View leave applications from my team members
Approve or reject leave requests with comments
View team leave calendar
View leave balance of team members
Receive in-app notifications when team member applies for leave
Performance Management Module:

Review performance documents submitted by direct reportees
Provide detailed feedback on employee performance reviews
Rate employee performance (1-5 scale or rating system)
Review employee goals and provide guidance
Track goal completion status of team members
Receive notifications when employee submits performance review
Generate team performance summary reports

Team Management:

View team structure and hierarchy
View team attendance summary
Access team member profiles

As an Admin, I should be able to:

Employee Management:

Add new employees with complete details:
Personal information (name, email, phone, address, DOB)
Employment details (employee ID, department, designation, joining date)
Manager assignment
Salary information
Update employee information
View all employee details
Deactivate/reactivate employee accounts
Assign/change reporting managers
Search employees by name, ID, department, or designation

Leave Management:

Configure leave types and policies

Assign leave quotas to employees:
Casual Leave (CL)
Sick Leave (SL)
Paid Leave (PL)
Privilege Leave
Adjust leave balances manually if needed
Revoke or cancel approved leaves (with manager approval)
View all employee leave information and statistics
Generate leave reports (department-wise, employee-wise)
Set company holiday calendar

System Configuration:

Manage departments and designations
Configure performance review cycles
Set system-wide policies
View system audit logs
Standard Functional Scope

Authentication & Security:

All registered users can log in using employee ID/email and password
Users can change their password (requires current password verification)
Forgotten password recovery through security questions or password reset by admin
Session management with automatic logout after inactivity

Notification System:

In-app notifications stored in database
Display unread notification count on login

Notification types:
Leave approval/rejection
Performance review feedback
Birthday/anniversary reminders
System announcements

p4-RevConnect
============

Application Overview

RevConnect is a console-based social media application that provides a platform for personal users, businesses, and content creators to connect and interact. Users can create posts, engage with content through likes and comments, build their network through connections and follows, and manage their profiles. The application is designed with a modular architecture that can be extended to a microservices-based web/mobile application in future phases.

Core Functional Requirements

As a Personal User, I should be able to:

Authentication & Profile:

Register and create an account with email and password
Login to my account
Create and edit basic profile with:
Name
Bio/About section
Profile picture path (for future use)
Location
Website link (optional)
View my profile and other users' profiles
Search for users by name or username

Post Management:

Create text posts with optional hashtags
View my posts and feed
Edit posts created by me
Delete posts created by me
View posts from connections and followed accounts in feed

Social Interactions:

Like posts (own and others')
Unlike posts
Comment on posts
View all comments on a post
Delete my own comments
Share/repost content (with attribution to original poster)

Network Building:

Send connection requests to other personal users
Accept or reject incoming connection requests
View pending connection requests
View my connections list
Remove connections
Follow business accounts and creator accounts
Unfollow accounts
View followers list
View following list

Notifications:

Receive in-app notifications for:
Connection requests received
Connection requests accepted
New followers
Likes on my posts
Comments on my posts
Shares of my posts
Posts from followed business/creator accounts
View unread notification count
Mark notifications as read
View notification history

Feed & Discovery:

View personalized feed with posts from:
My connections
Accounts I follow
My own posts
View trending posts/hashtags
Search posts by hashtags
Filter feed by post type or user type
As a Creator/Business Account User, I should be able to:

Note: Creator and Business accounts have all personal user features plus the following:

Profile Management:

Register as a creator or business account
Create enhanced profile with:
Business/Creator name
Category/Industry
Detailed bio
Business address (for business accounts)
Contact information
Website and social media links
Business hours (for business accounts)
Add multiple external links for business endorsements/partnerships
Showcase products/services (business accounts)

Content Creation:

Create promotional posts
Add call-to-action buttons to posts (future: "Learn More", "Shop Now")
Tag products/services in posts
Schedule posts (store for future posting - simulated)
View post analytics:
Total likes
Total comments
Total shares
Reach (number of unique viewers)

Engagement:

Like and comment on other users' posts
View followers and follower demographics
Respond to comments on business/creator posts
Pin important posts to profile

Business Features:

Create business pages
Post updates and announcements
Share promotional content
Interact with customers/followers
Standard Functional Scope

Authentication & Security:

All registered users can log in using email/username and password
Users can change their password (requires current password verification)
Forgotten password recovery through security questions or password hint
Account privacy settings (public/private profiles)

Notification System:

In-app notifications stored in database
Display unread notification count on login
Categorized notifications (connections, likes, comments, follows)
Notification preferences (enable/disable specific notification types)

Optional Features (Nice to Have):

Chat/Messaging:

Send direct messages to connections
View message history
Mark messages as read/unread
Delete conversations
Block users from messaging

P5-RevPay
========

Application Overview


RevPay is a console-based financial application that enables secure digital payments and money management for both personal and business users. Personal users can send/request money, manage payment methods, and track transactions. Business users gain additional capabilities including loan applications, payment acceptance, and invoice management. The application is designed with a modular architecture emphasizing security and transaction integrity, enabling future extension to a microservices-based web/mobile application.


Core Functional Requirements

As a Personal Account User, I should be able to:

Register and create a personal account with full name, email, phone number, password, and security questions
Login to my account using email/phone and password
Send money to other users by username, email, phone number, or account ID with amount and optional note
Request money from other users and view/manage incoming and outgoing money requests (accept/decline/cancel)
Add and manage payment methods including credit/debit cards with encrypted storage and the ability to set default payment method
View comprehensive transaction history with filtering by type, date range, amount, and status, plus search and export capabilities
Manage wallet balance by adding money from cards or withdrawing to bank accounts (simulated)
Receive in-app notifications for transactions, money requests, card changes, and low balance alerts
 

As a Business Account User,

I should be able to:

Note: Business accounts have all personal account features plus the following:

 

Register as a business account with business name, type, tax ID, address, and verification documents
Add business payment methods including business credit/debit cards and bank accounts
Accept payments from customers by generating payment requests/invoices and processing payments via multiple lookup methods
Create and manage invoices with itemized details, customer information, payment terms, and track paid/unpaid status
Apply for business loans with loan amount, purpose, financial information, and supporting documents, then track application status and manage repayments
View business analytics including transaction summaries, revenue reports, outstanding invoices, payment trends, and top customers
Send invoice notifications to customers (in-app) and manage payment acceptance
 

Standard Functional Scope

Authentication & Security:

Login, password change with current password + PIN verification
Forgotten password recovery through security questions
Account lockout after failed attempts, session timeout
Password hashing (bcrypt), card encryption (AES-256)
Transaction PIN separate from login password
Simulated two-factor authentication via security codes
Notification System:

In-app notifications for all transaction activities
Notification preferences and read/unread status tracking
Categorized by type (transactions, requests, alerts)

P6-RevHire
========

Application Overview

RevHire is a console-based job portal application that connects job seekers with employers. Job seekers can create profiles, build resumes, search for jobs, and apply to positions. Employers can post job openings, manage applications, and shortlist/reject candidates. The application is designed with a modular architecture that can be extended to a microservices-based web application in future phases.

Core Functional Requirements

As a Job Seeker, I should be able to:

Register and create an account with personal details
Login to my account
Create and manage textual resume with structured sections (objective, education, experience, skills, projects)
Search for jobs using filters (job role, location, experience years, company name, salary range, job type)
Apply for jobs with one-click using saved resume and optional cover letter (unlimited applications)
View all my applications with job details and status (Applied/Shortlisted/Rejected/Withdrawn)
Withdraw applications from jobs with confirmation and optional reason
Manage profile including education, work experience, skills, and certifications
Receive in-app notifications for application status updates and job matches

As an Employer, I should be able to:

Register company and create account with company details (name, industry, size, description, website, location)
Login using registered credentials
Create job postings with comprehensive details (title, description, skills, experience, education, location, salary, job type, deadline)
Manage job postings (view, edit, close/reopen, delete, view statistics)
View applicant details for each job including profile, resume, and application date
Shortlist or reject applications with bulk actions, comments, and status updates
Search and filter applicants by experience, skills, education, and application date
Manage company profile and update company information
Standard Functional Scope

Authentication & Account Management:

Register (separate flows for job seekers and employers)
Login using email and password
Change password (requires current password)
Forgotten password recovery through security questions
Profile completion tracking

Notification System:

In-app notifications for application status changes, new applications, and job matches

P7 - Password MAnager

Application Overview

The Password Manager is a secure console-based application that allows users to safely store and manage passwords for their various online accounts. Users can create an account with a master password, log in, generate strong random passwords, store account credentials, and manage their password vault. The application emphasizes security through password encryption and master password protection.

Core Functional Requirements

As a User, I should be able to:

Create an account to securely manage my passwords
Log in to my account to access the application
Update my profile information like name and email
Generate strong random passwords by providing parameters like string length, characters, numbers, etc.
List all the passwords with the respective account names
View individual password details (with master password re-entry)
Add new password entries for various accounts
Update existing passwords
Delete password entries
Search passwords by account name
Add security questions for account recovery
Get a verification code for sensitive operations which expires after use
Manage security questions linked to my account
Standard Functional Scope

Registered users should be able to log in, change the password and request for a forgotten password (recovered through security questions).

Definition of Done

Working console application demonstration
Sharing the associates' code repo for technical evaluation with:
ERD Diagram
Application Architecture Diagram (showing modular/layered design)